import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import numpy as np
google_df = df[df['company'] == 'Google']
google_df['totalyearlycompensation'] = google_df['totalyearlycompensation'] / 100000
x = google_df['yearsatcompany']
y = google_df['totalyearlycompensation']

slope, intercept = np.polyfit(x, y ,1)
y_fit = slope * x + intercept
plt.figure(figsize=(10,6))
plt.scatter(x,y ,alpha = 0.5)
plt.plot(x,y_fit , 'r', label = f'Best fit line: y = {slope:.2f}x + {intercept:.2f}')
plt.xlabel('Years Of Experience at Google')
plt.ylabel('Total Yearly Compensation')
plt.title('Years of Experience at Google Vs Total Yearly Compensation')
plt.grid(True)
plt.show()

In [32]:
companies_colors = {
    'Google': 'red',
    'Amazon': 'blue',
    'Facebook': 'green',
    'Microsoft': 'purple',
    'Apple': 'black'
}

# Create a scatter plot
plt.figure(figsize=(12, 8))

# Loop through each company and plot data
for company, color in companies_colors.items():
    # Filter data for each company
    company_df = df[df['company'] == company]
    
    # Convert total yearly compensation to units of $100,000
    company_df['totalyearlycompensation'] = company_df['totalyearlycompensation'] / 100000

    # Prepare data for regression line
    x = company_df['yearsatcompany']
    y = company_df[f'totalyearlycompensation']

    # Calculate coefficients for the line of best fit
    slope, intercept = np.polyfit(x, y, 1)
    y_fit = slope * x + intercept

    # Plot the raw data and the line of best fit
    plt.scatter(x, y, alpha=0.5, color=color, label=f'{company} (Data)')
    plt.plot(x, y_fit, color=color, label=f'{company} Best Fit Line: y = {slope:.2f}x + {intercept:.2f}')

# Add labels, title, and legend
plt.title('Yearly Compensation vs. Years at Company for Tech Companies (in $100,000s)')
plt.xlabel('Years at Company')
plt.ylabel('Total Yearly Compensation (in $100,000s)')
plt.legend()
plt.grid(True)
plt.show()

import seaborn as sns

companies_of_interest = ['Google', 'Amazon', 'Facebook', 'Microsoft', 'Apple']
filtered_dt = df[df['company'].isin(companies_of_interest)]

# Create a box plot
plt.figure(figsize=(14, 8))
sns.boxplot(x='level', y='totalyearlycompensation', hue='company', data=filtered_dt, palette='Set2')

plt.title('Yearly Compensation by Level for Selected Tech Companies')
plt.xlabel('Level')
plt.ylabel('Total Yearly Compensation (USD)')
plt.xticks(rotation=45)
plt.legend(title='Company')
plt.grid(True)
plt.show()

companies_of_interest = ['Google', 'Amazon', 'Facebook', 'Microsoft', 'Apple']
